Avoid using both Yarn and NPM

Having both `yarn.lock` and `package-lock.json` (i.e. using both Yarn and NPM) could [easily](https://github.com/yarnpkg/yarn/issues/5654) [be](https://github.com/yarnpkg/yarn/issues/3614) [problematic](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44552348/should-i-commit-yarn-lock-and-package-lock-json-files). In short, it creates a risk of out-of-sync where one author installs with NPM and forgot to update yarn.lock so another author, when using yarn, won't have that dependency.

In this PR I propose to drop the use of yarn in favor of NPM since a search in the codebase yields more NPM usages (especially in the doc and in package.json) than Yarn (only in Docker file to install).

If others have strong reasons for using Yarn over NPM then feel free to yield them. I don't have strong personal reason for one over another :D
Remove custom font reference in HTML

Remove custom font

As explained in #179, the custom font is unnecessary for our situation and removing it could help improving page load significantly.

Note that removing our option means that the default font choice of Bootstrap will be used. Since we are on version 4, it will be a [native font stack](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.5/content/reboot/#native-font-stack) which I think is really good for our case because there would be no loading or fetching at all.

Avoid using both Yarn and NPM

Having both `yarn.lock` and `package-lock.json` (i.e. using both Yarn and NPM) could [easily](https://github.com/yarnpkg/yarn/issues/5654) [be](https://github.com/yarnpkg/yarn/issues/3614) [problematic](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44552348/should-i-commit-yarn-lock-and-package-lock-json-files). In short, it creates a risk of out-of-sync where one author installs with NPM and forgot to update yarn.lock so another author, when using yarn, won't have that dependency.

In this PR I propose to drop the use of yarn in favor of NPM since a search in the codebase yields more NPM usages (especially in the doc and in package.json) than Yarn (only in Docker file to install).

If others have strong reasons for using Yarn over NPM then feel free to yield them. I don't have strong personal reason for one over another :D
Remove custom font reference in HTML
Remove custom font

As explained in #179, the custom font is unnecessary for our situation and removing it could help improving page load significantly.

Note that removing our option means that the default font choice of Bootstrap will be used. Since we are on version 4, it will be a [native font stack](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.5/content/reboot/#native-font-stack) which I think is really good for our case because there would be no loading or fetching at all.
